<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A globally hashed type represents a hash value that is sufficient to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="69"><Highlight kind="comment">/// uniquely identify a record across multiple type streams or type sequences.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This works by, for any given record A which references B, replacing the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><Highlight kind="comment">/// TypeIndex that refers to B with a previously-computed global hash for B.  As</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="72"><Highlight kind="comment">/// this is a recursive algorithm (e.g. the global hash of B also depends on the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><Highlight kind="comment">/// global hashes of the types that B refers to), a global hash can uniquely</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="74"><Highlight kind="comment">/// identify that A occurs in another stream that has a completely</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="75"><Highlight kind="comment">/// different graph structure.  Although the hash itself is slower to compute,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="76"><Highlight kind="comment">/// probing is much faster with a globally hashed type, because the hash itself</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="77"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is considered &quot;as good as&quot; the original type.  Since type records can be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="78"><Highlight kind="comment">/// quite large, this makes the equality comparison of the hash much faster than</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="79"><Highlight kind="comment">/// equality comparison of a full record.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="80" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/codeview/globallyhashedtype"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">struct </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/codeview/globallyhashedtype/#a9d71869a4b3222d94a767d6acaf44bfb">GloballyHashedType</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="81" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/codeview/globallyhashedtype/#a9d71869a4b3222d94a767d6acaf44bfb"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/codeview/globallyhashedtype/#a9d71869a4b3222d94a767d6acaf44bfb">GloballyHashedType</a>() = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">default</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
